EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging President Barack Obama to issue an Executive Order to the United States Treasury to put a woman on the twenty dollar bill by 2020, marking the 100th Anniversary of the 19th Amendment granting women the right to vote, and also calling upon the Secretary of the United States Treasury to support, and the Congress of the United States to pass S. 925 and H.R. 1910, the Woman on the Twenty Act, to replace Andrew Jackson on the twenty dollar bill with a woman who has played a prominent role in United States history.
EventItemMatterName: The Woman on the Twenty Act (S. 925 / H.R. 1910)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the seizure of abandoned bicycles.
EventItemMatterName: Seizure of abandoned bicycles.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the rights and responsibilities of tenants and owners regarding the lawful collection of rents.
EventItemMatterName: Rights and responsibilities of tenants and owners regarding the lawful collection of rents.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A.4762 and S.1291, which would extend labor protections to farm workers.
EventItemMatterName: Extend labor protections to farm workers. (A.4762/S.1291)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon Gerawan Farming to respect their workers, and implement the agreement ordered by the contract terms set by the mediator
EventItemMatterName: Gerawan Farming to respect their workers, and implement the agreement ordered by the contract terms set by the mediator.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Nuclear Regulatory Commission not to relicense Indian Point 2 and Indian Point 3, so that those reactors will cease operations, and calling upon New York State to work with affected workers, local officials, and environmental groups to develop and implement a socially, economically, and environmentally just transition plan to address the needs of displaced employees and local communities.
EventItemMatterName: United States Nuclear Regulatory Commission not to relicense Indian Point 2 and Indian Point 3.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to extending the transfer tax exemption period for leases of taxicab licenses
EventItemMatterName: Extending the transfer tax exemption period for leases of taxicab licenses.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring Community Board referral of certificate of appropriateness applications and subsequent modifications
EventItemMatterName: Requiring Community Board referral of certificate of appropriateness applications and subsequent modifications.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, A2529/S857, allowing 16 and 17 year-olds to pre-register to vote.
EventItemMatterName: Allowing 16 and 17 year-olds to pre-register to vote. (A2529/S857)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the human resources administration to provide rental assistance to disabled veterans
EventItemMatterName: Requiring HRA to provide rental assistance to disabled veterans.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Veterans
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to creating a taskforce to study veterans in the criminal justice system
EventItemMatterName: Creating a taskforce to study veterans in the criminal justice system.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Veterans
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on Congress to pass and the President to sign the Servicemember Assistance for Lawful Understanding, Treatment and Education (SALUTE) Act of 2015
EventItemMatterName: Servicemember Assistance for Lawful Understanding, Treatment and Education (SALUTE) Act of 2015.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Economic Development
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York City Economic Development Corporation to establish a centralized veterans-exclusive incubator in the City.
EventItemMatterName: Economic Development Corporation to establish a centralized veterans-exclusive incubator in the City.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the creation of a task force to assess safety risks at construction sites
EventItemMatterName: Creation of a task force to assess safety risks at construction sites.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to bicycle access in office buildings
EventItemMatterName: Clarifying bicycle access in office buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation to establish an Innocence Inquiry Commission to investigate credible post-conviction claims of innocence.
EventItemMatterName: Establish an Innocence Inquiry Commission.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to implementing a pilot project to reduce the number of crashes involving city owned motor vehicles.
EventItemMatterName: Implementing a pilot project to reduce the number of crashes involving city owned motor vehicles.
